In this statement, President Barack Obama praises Secretary Gates for advancing efforts to invest in defense capabilities while being responsible with taxpayer dollars. The President emphasizes the need to change the way Washington works and make government more open and responsive to the American public. He highlights the importance of reducing waste and inefficiency in national defense to better serve the men and women in uniform and invest in future capabilities. The President commends Secretary Gates for taking steps to reduce excess overhead costs, cut waste, and reform the way the Pentagon does business. The funds saved will be used to sustain the current force structure and make necessary investments in modernization. Overall, these reforms aim to strengthen national security and ensure fiscal responsibility.